main event: An unidentified aerial object was sighted in Pacific Beach, Washington, on 16 March 1950.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 4 minutes with the object changing bearings to 270 degrees on departure., The object was described as decelerating to a comparatively slow speed., It executed a series of incoherent movements while maintaining its position., No weather conditions, color, or exhaust trail were reported during the sighting., There were no sketches or photographs available.
